        category: 'Labor',
        date: 'March 21st, 1877',
        title: `Farmers' Alliance Founded (1877)`,
        imgSrc: require('./assets/eventPhotos/Organizations/farmersAlliance.jpg'),
        description: `The Farmers Alliance was an organized agrarian economic movement among American farmers that was founded on this day in 1877. The movement was an alliance of several independent farming organizations and a multi-racial coalition. It was heavily associated with the People's Party (known as the "Populist" movement).\n\n The Alliance was formed to combat predation of poor farmers by banks and industrialists in a time of economic hardship for the agricultural industry. In 1889, a bushel of corn had lost 80% of its value from a few decades prior, and 90% of southern farmers relied on credit to survive. Around the same time, it boasted over 400,000 members.\n\nThe Farmers' Alliance collectively bargained for equipment prices, formed a statewide cooperative in Texas to handle the selling of equipment, and advocated for government reforms that would ease the financial burden on farmers, introducing more money into circulation in particular. In 1892, their presidential candidate, James Weaver, received over a million votes. After allying with the Democratic Party, the Alliance and the People's Party collapsed in 1896.`,
        link: 'https://www.historyisaweapon.com/defcon1/zinnbaron11.html',
        infoSrc: 'https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Farmers%27_Alliance'
