        imgSrc: require('./assets/eventPhotos/Events/bombardmentOfGreytown.jpg'),
        description: `The Bombardment of Greytown or the Bombardment of San Juan del Norte was a naval action initiated by the United States warship USS Cyane against the town of Greytown in the Miskito Kingdom (modern day Nicaragua). The town was completely destroyed by massive fires set by marines who came ashore. The attack was in response to attempts by the British government to charge taxes on ships that used the town as a port, among other grievances.\n\nIn response to international outrage regarding the incident, president Franklin Pierce issued a statement acknowledging that, while it would have been more satisfactory if the Cyane's mission could have been consummated without the use of force, "the arrogant contumacy of the offenders rendered it impossible to avoid the alternative either to break up their establishment or to leave them impressed with the idea that they might persevere with impunity in a career of insolence and plunder."`,
