        imgSrc: require('./assets/eventPhotos/Individuals/sheldonWolin.jpg'),
        description: `Sheldon Sanford Wolin, born on this day in 1922, was an American political theorist and writer on contemporary politics. A political theorist for fifty years, Wolin became Professor of Politics, Emeritus, at Princeton University, where he taught from 1973 to 1987.\n\nWolin's political thought is particularly concerned with the fate of democracy at the hands of bureaucratic imperatives, elitism, and managerial principles and practices. His concepts of "inverted totalitarianism" and "fugitive democracy" are a particularly important legacy of his work.`,
