        title: 'Acteal Massacre (1997)',
        imgSrc: require('./assets/eventPhotos/Events/actealMassacre.jpg'),
        description: `The Acteal Massacre was committed by a right-wing paramilitary group on this day in 1997, against forty-five members of the pacifist Las Abejas ("The Bees"), sympathizers of the Zapatistas, who were attending a prayer meeting in Chiapas. The killing took place in the small village of Acteal in the municipality of Chenalhó, and among the people murdered were a number of children and pregnant women.\n\nLas Abejas had earlier professed their support for the goals of the Zapatista Army of National Liberation (EZLN). The right-wing paramilitary group Máscara Roja ("Red Mask") took responsibility for the attack initially, however in July of 2020, the Mexican government admitted to some culpability in the killings.`,
